[{"Name":"Olivia Spatz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6md6GkwA9jOXdLCudZ7HUmiM4PcG9-l7pLNZ8yo1ishSVLl4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
McMullan‚Äôs Irish Pub is an absolute gem!

We ordered the Coast Road Inn Fish & Chips, and even though I normally don‚Äôt care for fried foods, this quickly became my favorite dish, perfectly crisp, fresh, and surprisingly light. Nanny Mac‚Äôs Shepherd‚Äôs Pie was warm, cozy, and delicious, served with hearty brown bread that made the dish even better.

We also tried the Homemade Crisps, which were a nice light appetizer with tasty Marie Rose and curry sauces. For dessert, the Sticky Toffee Pudding had a wonderful bread-pudding, like texture and just the right sweetness. And you must try their famous Irish Coffee, the cream on top was whipped to absolute perfection.

Everything tasted fresh, clean, and high-quality. The service was excellent too, very welcoming, and our server was incredibly knowledgeable. A fun pub with great food and great vibes. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDpu6Yk4kZGXvmaov_4FcNR&fid=0x0:0x349acad40e1aeb15"],"When":"2025-11-30"},{"Name":"Jakob","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4kwYAwAQH557N5kfUT0wW2j4pF8Iy7oThfdBrzsVBWz8HqoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here when friends were visiting from out of town. Service was pretty good. There was one point where I wondered if we were going to be checked on for beverages, but for the most part, our server was good. Atmosphere is awesome. Can get a little loud with sporting events but it‚Äôs not that bad.
As for the food‚Ä¶it was pretty good. The three that were with me enjoyed what they ordered. I got the corned beef sandwich, and it was dry. Hardly any mustard. I didn‚Äôt really taste much of it at all, so if you order it, get an extra side of mustard.
Wouldn‚Äôt prevent me from returning to try something different.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhC7_mqisVUUHUlEJunkXwXt&fid=0x0:0x349acad40e1aeb15"],"When":"2026-2-2"},{"Name":"Pamela C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXynMou96IMuQcU7L0cfbqVg-cKeVQiaOqvYfvUP7rhsomP-bbB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down one of my favorite places to eat in Vegas. It is a locals favorite!

The service is great everyone was friendly and all of their recommendations I loved.

I have been 4 times on my stay in Vegas and will be going back again this week before I head home.

You won‚Äôt be disappointed-  go try McMullan‚Äôs!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBp51WaVELTcoSs4cx0OYmM&fid=0x0:0x349acad40e1aeb15"],"When":"2025-12-15"},{"Name":"Colin Waring","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMNa-JwOgM0NWE9cYdqRVpgE77jHLJTvKtgvlel7QcBLf58GY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely old pub with lots of footy memorabilia especially for the Red Men. Prices very reasonable especially Guinness. A great menu of pub grub, home from home cooking and then some. Separate area to watch the match amongst footy fans. Busy place for the big games. Ross and team made everyone welcome and table service was a huge bonus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhB8uleZqvOgRme0GwS89hNp&fid=0x0:0x349acad40e1aeb15"],"When":"2025-11-7"},{"Name":"P Murphy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYRwhaHPvAyjc-b96V2ai8IxNMtXDllN-0Gdh4g4bBUF0y70Wf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A very authentic Irish pub inside and out.  Our server Jennifer C was fantastic.  We stopped in for a couple of drinks and a quick appetizer.  The Irish Nachos were delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCfXvmAZkdWiwsEsLA-x53S&fid=0x0:0x349acad40e1aeb15"],"When":"2026-1-18"},{"Name":"Issa Meboe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUOslobps73wuJkh_YEReDpZPaM5GrWBPRRp2eX1daTmBI5plML=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Excellent! Decent prices for great food, and what an array of choices. There's something for everyone here. The authentic food is beautiful and the portions are significant. The corned beef and cabbage with their homemade bread was flavorful, filling, and hearty. A real home cooked meal.
The only thing I personally don't enjoy is the smoke atmosphere, but as long as you don't stay in the bar area it's not really a problem. The noise is also significant if you want to have conversations at dinner, but the more private dining area made it much easier. Great service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhD9XAx34AvPoxEEJLas1wnR&fid=0x0:0x349acad40e1aeb15"],"When":"2025-9-19"},{"Name":"Laurie Ruthe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdr4a4a4mzudOESRaTLMjNMAjoSx-KvCP5_he1Dt-iQ8cUdICN=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Popped by on an afternoon and enjoyed dining on the outdoor deck! Adam took great care of us! You‚Äôll never love an Irish Coffee as much, after having one here! They are simply The Best!! Our fav Irish Pub! ‚òòÔ∏è  As usual, the food was fabulous too!  ~ Irish Coffee ~ Wild Salmon ~ Ann‚Äôs Blackened Chicken Salad üíØ See you again soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDN8ONa4D6CvfL_mmeJABMp&fid=0x0:0x349acad40e1aeb15"],"When":"2025-10-7"},{"Name":"Zenon Skyy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI2Zj8GaHkA5uOg-7-XR3PBRYEThlS8vAifeL2Iio0ER0qqRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"12/31/25

It‚Äôs very nice to see that your whole building is being painted. It‚Äôll give your businesses, and the adjoining ones, a very much needed fresh look. Now if only there was an effective way to deter the vagrants and hookers (Not your fault, I know).

The food is always great, as are the drinks, and service. It‚Äôs too bad that the loyalty program has gone by the wayside, with the annual birthday gift.

Have you thought about having both sides of all of your doors painted/re-stained? And the small shelves in the bar area. The wear is really showing, and it doesn‚Äôt look vintage, but neglected rather.

Unfortunately, you have quite a few pieces of graffiti on the walls in your main men's room. And it's been there for some time. You really have a classy place and should have somebody remove it. Because it‚Äôs looking like the Dive Bar and Double Down Saloon.

Also, consider replacing the soap dispenser in the main men‚Äôs room. And right outside it, a picture on the wall has been missing for quite some time.

Oh, and you have graffiti on the Cameron side of your building.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhA5b_3RgMBX-aLReQwBGxbq&fid=0x0:0x349acad40e1aeb15"],"When":"2025-12-9"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jeffrey Cui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNpkAOKmkEVocO7J-TW3Uj_8JgIssX0AbITIFlD5n8CZidriAD3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a sports bar in the Tuscany Hotel and Casino, we ate here a couple of times during our stay there.  The restaurant is a typical sports bar atmosphere with a bar and tables for patrons.  The staff was friendly and professional.  Our first visit the waitress was not as attentive as you‚Äôd expect but the second experience more than made up for it.  My son and his girlfriend had baja fish tacos one fried and one grilled, they said they enjoyed theirs but agreed the grilled was better.  I had the Unicorn burger which was a big patty with lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and onion rings. It was pretty big and hearty, I enjoyed it.  We recommend it if you‚Äôre in the area‚Ä¶.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBFCtqmkY9B0rVkhloOzR7g&fid=0x0:0x55d73c5f48c04b34"],"When":"2025-11-23"},{"Name":"Ari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUts54Jf6LTm7SzxeW09ccrGfOqSssRd0f66ZfxBUFR8vWCgJSE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had to see what all the buzz was about and I get it! This was my first visit, and I can confidently say it's a solid go-to whether you're grabbing a casual bite or planning a full night out. The vibe strikes the perfect balance: lively and energetic without feeling overwhelming. It's the kind of place where you can kick back, relax, and enjoy great company.
Now, the food? Absolutely delicious. The menu covers everything from classic pub fare to more creative, elevated dishes. I went with the Korean Ribs, Crispy Baja Fish Tacos, and couldn‚Äôt pass up the late-night special: steak & eggs for just $8.99. Every dish hit the mark, full of flavor, no misses. While I didn‚Äôt get a chance to drinks, the bar menu looked stacked with craft beers, cocktails, and a solid wine list. On top of it all, the staff were super friendly and welcoming, which really made the experience stand out. This spot has definitely earned a place on my list of Vegas favorites.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCGT5VNK_pO1NP-t6dzf2II&fid=0x0:0x55d73c5f48c04b34"],"When":"2025-9-18"},{"Name":"Alex A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ1UDwwo8zGcsWexoYE8CgsCbb5wVpqiqTuwAFbbIPggllGjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Outstanding spot for a night out or a casual meal. The food is consistently delicious, with a menu that has something for everyone, from hearty pub classics to creative dishes. The drinks are top notch, and they have a great selection of beers, cocktails, and wines. The staff is friendly, welcoming, and attentive, making you feel right at home every time. The atmosphere is lively yet comfortable, perfect for catching up with friends or enjoying a relaxed evening. It‚Äôs definitely one of my favorite spots in Vegas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhByWAvZsU2kUxvEB0rmrAM9&fid=0x0:0x55d73c5f48c04b34"],"When":"2025-8-26"},{"Name":"Courtney Marie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMrhDnPkcczcZr7ol-wvFqJZ4aKzZbFCZLiP6wDdW161caOW4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this place and make a point to visit every time I‚Äôm in Vegas. The chicken wings are so good.. great beer selection, bartenders are friendly. And I recognize the same faces there from years back, I always think that‚Äôs a good sign! Must be a good place to work.
My only gripe- they got rid of the Tom burger (long time ago) and I still dream about it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"M Nedloc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUF99_XP3XRfRB6nXx6HkTWvwYHSs6vmJzq-C9WiUF1olSc_ek=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Decent sized restaurant is in Tuscany Suites and Casino. We were cutting it short, and the staff was kind enough to take us in. Everything was hot and not too shabby. It was of course a late night in Las Vegas, just glad we could grab something a little more than fast food. The parking here is pretty good, never had a hard time doing so. Everything was served in a timely manner, prices were good, and everyone enjoyed their meal. Try the deep fried Oreos!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgICHhOC55QE&fid=0x0:0x55d73c5f48c04b34"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"J. Travels","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlXGQ1hGiyFaQk3HnmyFVq3lJd9yxty3rvpJenquvDblqP9yzqOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pub 365 east Flamingo Road. Las vegas Nevada.  Excellent 8.99 newyork strip steak, potatoes, and eggs after 10 p.m. deal. along with the Choclate Lava cake, for desert.  Can't go wrong. I got 2 of them steaks for myself.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCa2ao9lx7HGGufeIYNiQ90&fid=0x0:0x55d73c5f48c04b34"],"When":"2025-7-4"},{"Name":"Ajinkya Shinde","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIasBi7ZNqf1xm7Yjd7C3lpCVvGDPOl1UfHxbz0HAJwbDpFng=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is really good. Was staying at Tuscany and went to Pub late at 11:30. Kitchen was still open and Randall at the bar was so attentive and excellent service. Food was great, drink was fantastic. I went again the second night and Jose was the bartender. Excellent service again, friendly and attentive. I had crispy fish tacos and trust me they were the best tacos I ever had. Had 2 drinks. Staff is very polite and attentive. Everything was great esp. shout-out to Randall and Jose.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kei Chua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3PkDuPSNQHISR1k02q1yuwhThlWfU7fHei1RmC12uq2bnR41C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here for the late night steak and eggs deal.  Starts at 10:00pm.  It's set up like a sports bar so quite noisy between the loud music and everyone trying to shout over the music to speak with the person next to them.  At least the place was clean.

Almost everybody there ordered the special.  The servers are quick and efficient.

Unfortunately the casino area was dead.  We did a quick round after dinner, but the Black Jack table was full, so they got us in with the special, but because of the lack of table games we didn't spend anytime in the casino.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBuD2dk9U43Kn2LSayClCAT&fid=0x0:0x55d73c5f48c04b34"],"When":"2025-8-13"}]

One of the home boys made the shot and everyone in the place got free shot!!!!!! Pour straight into our mouths, what a time to remember. The staff is AMAZING!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgMCgzqaLPg\u0026fid=0x0:0x3c4f6bce99a82eeb"],"When":"2025-2-17"},{"Name":"DEE Jax","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIzmfyaoLyahXqeJj0EyaFhy57yWkJOJ0kVRTx6XTxy7Nzf5Kp4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved this spot! First time going and I will always go there every time im in Vegas. Bartenders were awesome and those bottle tricks they did were cool. The buy 1 get 1 free deal is LEGIT! Also those drinks were very strong...it only took two to have me tap out! Good prices too!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rafael Flores","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLo_56X9wAKJnl5o00mfW8zytGDNO6I-6T98uWlAqBvqM2d6M=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We recently visited in the first few days of January after several years of initially having a horrible experience; in the hopes things had gotten better. Well I can tell you they haven‚Äôt. Me and my female friend entered the bar late one night to get a drink and keep our night going. Upon entering the staff was extremely friendly and lively and welcoming, especially Paul and Colby. They asked us if we knew about their current promotion and how it worked so we could get a good deal. As we sat at the bar top a group of two males and two females who all looked like they were in the mid 40‚Äôs attempted to get my attention. I turned over to them and they began to ask extremely sexual and inappropriate questions about my friend and if we were in the mood to party. Instead of reacting out of anger and this situation leading to a worse one I told them off and said leave us alone. They didn‚Äôt like this and proceeded to make degrading and negative sexual comments about myself and my friend. I immediately notified our bartender who reacted promptly and notified the bar manager. The bar manager then approached the guests who of course denied everything and in a dramatic and obvious move of being caught in the act got up and left the bar. Then I noticed the bar manager get on his phone. After talking with the staff we were told these were regulars at the bar. The team did apologize for their behavior and made it clear that it is not okay for anyone to be doing this to any other patrons. We continued to enjoy our drinks and shortly after the owner showed up welcoming back in the regulars who had just gotten kicked out. He spent about 20min speaking with them and laughing. Not once did he come over to me and my friend to apologize to us or explain why he felt it to be okay to allow such guests back in while we were still here. If this is the type of regulars this owner allows then it speaks volumes for the lack of consideration and care he has of any other business. Once again the staff did a great job checking in on us and in the end taking care of the bill as a sign of good will; which they did not have to do at all.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Miranda Fraunfelter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgBdN9w8f4Ecz_NIVuwTCbWuCZbd7klIZqdOff2TW43UECPteXig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This may be one of Vegas best kept secrets. The restaurant is in Ellis Island casino. You receive coupons for their restaurants with game play. The ribs were fall off the bone and the sauce was really good. The steak was cooked to order and very good. All of the sides were very good as well but no way we could finish it all. Two great tasting enormous meals in Vegas for under $30 is a win! It is a block off of the strip, close to the Sphere, and open 24/7 for a good meal before or after a show.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhB1c82VNCaGlUY9XN_JI_Oo&fid=0x0:0xdc15ac48d6e1dd96"],"When":"2025-12-23"},{"Name":"Nicole Manno","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGqRdabVQyp-t4GewFKiSJh8Zaoe4WHX3NS866ZthqtY9t0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best breakfast deal in vegas! Steak and eggs breakfast for less than $14. Steak is tender and the potatoes don‚Äôt look appealing but they taste great!! I was more than satisfied with the breakfast a the price. Although I don‚Äôt recommend the pancake ( it was kind of spongy and chewy) everything else was great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCvwZ77_wKeOgD0x92pHk9C&fid=0x0:0xdc15ac48d6e1dd96"],"When":"2026-1-27"},{"Name":"Todd P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUr1v6nPXocH0BUrQLcYdusjhpr4U6q-bWTBSFM2ecOCaabByzI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had a Las Vegas Advisor coupon for this restaurant. And we had always wanted to visit Ellis Island. The restaurant itself is pretty old-school. Not fancy at all, but reminiscent of an earlier era.

We had lunch here and ordered the Lumberjack burger and the fish and chips.  We also split one of their homemade root beers. The portions were extremely large and very very good. Especially the fish.  Our server told us that they bring in whole fish and fillet them on site. They were piping hot and crispy on the outside and flaky on the inside. The burger was also huge. We didn‚Äôt really care for the steak fries, though. The root beer was excellent. We recommend giving the pub a try if you are in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCGP4OB8tkdLVIT4AE-cG_C&fid=0x0:0xdc15ac48d6e1dd96"],"When":"2025-11-5"},{"Name":"Robert Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIVxEWmHG0y-p5675lMWL4xVWvs6FndFIN7J3m3JlOn9C90LQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is not fine dining.   But, it's good and reasonably priced diner food.  And you'll get a small discount, if you get a players card and gamble alittle bit in their casino.  There are times that you just want basic diner food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBImuRgQvuj0GveEg4DPgku&fid=0x0:0xdc15ac48d6e1dd96"],"When":"2025-12-17"},{"Name":"Henry WinePro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtOBOpXltKZpLwL21tX7OoR-QOOFXcA-rOBnJH3HnQ2-OH9E5dqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I want to express my sincere gratitude, first and foremost, to Priscilla, the charming hostess. Her exceptional service, professional demeanor, and genuine care made both of my visits truly special, and I look forward to returning largely because of her outstanding hospitality, as well as the food, of course. Her attentiveness, combined with the restaurant's commitment to quality, consistently transformed our meals into memorable experiences. I would also like to thank the kitchen staff for consistently preparing delicious meals. The excellence in food preparation, combined with the energetic and inviting ambiance, makes this restaurant a place I want to visit again, which reinforces the positive impression created by the front-of-house team. Last but not least, I would like to thank Yen for making me feel so welcome and at home during my initial visit, as well as for her efficiency, care, and delightful service. I would also like to thank Andrew for his excellent service during my second visit.

The only minor issue was that the French Onion Soup was a bit overdone on top when it was served to me; however, given the overall positive experience, I chose not to complain about it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAZ3Pu7Usn8rFIgNZc3w6P5&fid=0x0:0xdc15ac48d6e1dd96"],"When":"2025-7-23"},{"Name":"robert brenner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWs6Ha0rcHA1u3pZk0_0WbxxbUCaCiH6Qx6aq7JDsHAU_wmJK1x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It has been almost 15 years since we went to Ellis Island- back when the T-Bone and the beer was 9.99 and the craps table was a small tub. It‚Äôs still the same great place! We had the special, now $14.99! We had soup or salad to start and I got the clam chowder- fantastic! Then the sirloin, green beans and baked potato. I thought for sure the sirloin was going to be tough but it was tender and delicious. It was 12 ounces and so good. I was really impressed! We then played craps for $5 minimum and had a blast. What a great place to watch F1 too. For $100 you watch on the platform and get unlimited food and beer. Now that‚Äôs what I‚Äôm talking about. Still love Ellis Island. More great memories to share.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBZ5Qi9fOZ5qKUfS5-MqY2U&fid=0x0:0xdc15ac48d6e1dd96"],"When":"2025-11-22"},{"Name":"Billie Perrone","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW70MZ82N9sBfYgr8wYiAd-gZfMjmkBPME4rFhPdQTaz6zrxnPU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We both got medium king cut prime rib for $34.99 with potato, garlic green beans &salad. Got buy one get one free with players card & LV Advisor coupon. If you're a local, or visit a lot in a year, that coupon book is gold. $50 per year. Our server Ayanna was kind and friendly. Food came quick. Great food & service! Thanks!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCEiV8QNMzD--y8aBXp9uqX&fid=0x0:0xdc15ac48d6e1dd96"],"When":"2025-11-29"},{"Name":"Caleb Nino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqjrKUZVJ_PsyCcaOtofmjbg2toXmLndomRNucaC1RLZG6R14k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Haven‚Äôt been here in 5 years, it‚Äôs still just as perfect a spot as I remember!!!

Food was cooked perfectly, to order, Rocio - is one of the most hardworking servers I‚Äôve ever seen! She was an absolute joy to have serve me.

The only draw back to this place is everyone knows about it now. 5 years ago it was not as hard to get a table‚Ä¶ today I came in on a Saturday at 10 and it was SLAMMED. 30 minute wait just to get a spot for 1. (No bar service)

If you‚Äôre new:
- Best prices in the strip
- Food is better than most overpriced casino restaurants
- Pay attention to what times breakfast ends!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAOMNT_cIo0oYmPvplYrjbm&fid=0x0:0xdc15ac48d6e1dd96"],"When":"2026-1-24"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Pierce Colman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfo5bdeVzq3pf9BmK1TemWSunHwZF5Fk_J_QFRdB3O0TgMoH8o=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was a fun experience. Get ready to hike up some stairs but the top floor is a great vibe. We had a great server. The nachos were great and the extra beer cheese was a great suggestion by our server. My buddy got wings and I got the big rib burger. I‚Äôm a burger aficionado and save 5 stars for truly standout best burgers and this one was very good but I thought the short rib was a little dry but overall a pretty dang good burger. I would definitely go back and try out some more things on the menu. The margaritas were great too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAikhFh70p3hwlowtPdmyJG&fid=0x0:0x564531310cccd48b"],"When":"2026-2-1"},{"Name":"DG See","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwkohWP1pE6y_7Kk3U5VL9nxWCeEOLoKGcfwts-sJGLG6d5mY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely fantastic experience. The staff were incredibly friendly and welcoming from start to finish.
Their beer recommendations were spot on ‚Äî Wing Man and Hazy Jane were both outstanding and full of flavor.
Even though I had a short schedule and couldn‚Äôt stay long, the quality of the beers and the great service made it a memorable visit.
Highly recommended, and I will definitely come back next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhC13ZnQE94EcJZL78LUGWgU&fid=0x0:0x564531310cccd48b"],"When":"2026-1-9"},{"Name":"Debbie Hernandez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWy16G1-c5TQhksSHoe765yyg61Rv3hM0m7g_Ej0wyxILd0IoYl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Philip,  our server was outstanding! We ordered the loaded fries and requested a change in the meat.  The kitchen sent it out with the wrong meat. The lady that delivered it to our table, who had an attitude said we couldn't substitute the meat. I mentioned this to our server Philip and he went back to the kitchen and talk to them about the situation,  he brought us out the protein. He really turned around our meal! We also enjoyed a gluten-free chicken sandwich and piickel fries,which were delicious. We also enjoyed a variety of delicious cocktails! The views from the bar are outstanding!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhC7ALHDvSgTMnuaE_LlKOte&fid=0x0:0x564531310cccd48b"],"When":"2025-11-14"},{"Name":"Fernando Ortega","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKk9HVPJiY2EIyexbHEGhxlSh4LrvoxT-8A6Rnm3R7ACP_Qbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wanted to try a different place for wings besides your popular ones. The place in Vegas is located on the strip and is on the rooftop of the building with a view of the strip. Had the regular size 6 wings buffalo sauce. The sauce had great flavor and was perfect on the heat. The beer of choice for me was Modelo but the have beer from the Vegas area to complement your food. Service can use more help.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDT4ffG0YTabqH-T4nFnr7i&fid=0x0:0x564531310cccd48b"],"When":"2025-12-30"},{"Name":"Adam Hovak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVLZZ9-7M9IZAFo240T6AfgW9hcUkJrx6w4Tfh_60l5Ot0Imbt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stopped in because they said they had a rooftop bar and we were pleasantly surprised. 56 beers on tap and buy one get one free appetizers. We had the soft pretzel and the nachos, and both were good and both were huge. I don‚Äôt think 1 person could eat any one appetizer by themselves. View of the strip is a bit off center, but relatively unblocked. Stop in for a bite!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDgucfehUSsswbAvukCNwVe&fid=0x0:0x564531310cccd48b"],"When":"2026-1-18"},{"Name":"Robert Wilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDdPPjPDuYlyzi5k8OS53W1MZrKwezmS9RXDeYNp6fCg8HUzAn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A great, laid-back place to grab a beer and enjoy either the indoor seating or the outdoor seating overlooking the strip. Outdoors, there are plenty of heaters, and all the drinks they offer are great, including the non-alcoholic offerings as well. I visited twice during my trip as it was such an enjoyable experience, and I look forward to visiting again in the future!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAt_CCC1Rc4SmPf-VTX1NnU&fid=0x0:0x564531310cccd48b"],"When":"2025-12-3"},{"Name":"Blaine Losier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJ7A33TeZm72Pg8kemQ-ucbgig3pqA2sbvQZ7YjTK9ztJSkw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great spot for good craft beer and good food.  The burgers are amazing and they have a nice selection of really good micro-brews. The atmosphere is great and the rooftop patio gives you a great view of the strip. Will definitely be coming back here next time I visit Vegas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAteT7uMGkj0OuL1kMTk4gC&fid=0x0:0x564531310cccd48b"],"When":"2025-11-15"},{"Name":"JF Bruns","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8qj-3VnkslgAkXe5DRemXf82Ohdc96iDudG6GVhsdwe2p331t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"12/25 - Here on a Sunday just as the Raiders home game started - PERFECT.  A flight of beers & chicken wings, doesn't get better than this.  Had a great server which make the experience better.  Leaves a water carafe on the table, wonderful for my wife's condition.  Wing dry rub was a little spicier that the server let on, think of Tony Chacheres with a little brown sugar.  Sweet potato fries were good, maybe a little sweeter than I like. Overall, a good experience & will be back next year.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBlQlfeo7DHsPtXwC2heGTL&fid=0x0:0x564531310cccd48b"],"When":"2025-12-7"}]

ATL Expert 'Lv. 8 Local' (GoogleMaps Power Reviewer)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWu7UC4rHYMC7AZjVaYtsWt4Y9dakWSGevpveTm9nVhS1U75oTwsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I dined at Gordon Ramsay Pub & Grill and ordered the Wagyu Burger √† la carte, along with a course menu that included the Beef Wellington. It was a great experience because I was able to enjoy signature dishes from both Gordon Ramsay Burger and Hell‚Äôs Kitchen in one visit.

The Wagyu Burger was flavorful and satisfying, while the Beef Wellington in the course menu delivered the classic taste and presentation Gordon Ramsay restaurants are known for. Being able to try items associated with two of his most popular concepts made the meal especially enjoyable.

Another major plus was that no reservation was needed. Compared to Hell‚Äôs Kitchen, which often requires advance reservations and long wait times, Pub & Grill was much more relaxed and convenient.

Overall, Gordon Ramsay Pub & Grill is a great option if you want to sample Gordon Ramsay‚Äôs signature dishes without the hassle of reservations, while still enjoying solid food in a casual setting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCOmo_0kRwTyif49jFz-7wo&fid=0x0:0x8a173f9aeeee6ff0"],"When":"2025-12-25"},{"Name":"thegrey god","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIXpog8165hmDbNolhqcR9FDf0PJoeiWMnJwjgLUMwsVvuZGw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"French onion soup was bitter. Lobster shrimp roll was plain and without flavor, the toasted bread has more flavor.  The sauce for the Wellington was superb, the shell was a bit dough, the round ball of carrots and potatoes  (? Tasteless) were so hard you smacked your plate cutting through them. The dessert was excellent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAWEJNDQ1JPQQpzLA0sTAvI&fid=0x0:0x8a173f9aeeee6ff0"],"When":"2026-2-17"},{"Name":"Tracy Kohls","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbFmYh_Wcms8O3iMqQRT3rTzrqWH2XnQbYS39yTuf686levwk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We tried a few Gordon Ramsey options while in Vegas. Thumbs up on Ramsey‚Äôs pub n grill!

We liked the pub n grill atmosphere since was both casual or dressy and with a slightly lower cost option compared to Hells Kitchen or Ramsey Steaks Etc.

I had the 3 Course meal onion soup, w/Beef Wellington, sticky pudding ( ie chocolate type cake topped with vanilla bean ice cream/toffee drizzle)
***Definite 5 stars***
My husband had the 12 oz NewYork topped w Tiger shrimp & cheesy potato‚Äôs, also rated 5 stars.

Menu also offers several al la carte options and fish n chips, wagu burger, truffle fries‚Ä¶, so everyone can choose about anything at this location.
Location: Next to casino in Caesar‚Äôs just past the food court.
Attire: Resort Casual (even some wearing ball caps) up to dressy attire‚Ä¶
w/great beer pub bar & several TVs showing sporting events, as well. (but not loud tv noise)

Note: lunch rates for 3 course meal will be less if you dine ‚Äúbefore‚Äù the 3pm -12pm window
*Groupon periodically has discounts for all the Ramsey locations, so check it out before traveling and make reservations during busy periods.
Walk-ins ok for pub n grill.
I will return to this location when we visit again (mostly due to the slight savings if I bring the whole family)
Dinner: still expect to pay about $50-$100 per person or more w/alcohol or added sides. Fixed 3 course meal is a good value approx $89-$94 per person or about $70 for lunch. Other locations are about $130+ for the same fixed 3 course option.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBp96epxjg0UfUFBxWFd5Jz&fid=0x0:0x8a173f9aeeee6ff0"],"When":"2025-10-8"},{"Name":"Jessica Gustin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_jOGut1ezLi7yrgztaz5hwgIdfedhneHvGwfeTVMQn9320VFT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è
Gordon Ramsay‚Äôs Pub & Grill ‚Äì Las Vegas
We‚Äôve been to a few of Gordon Ramsay‚Äôs other restaurants and loved them, so we decided to give this one a try‚Äîand it did not disappoint! Our group ordered a variety of dishes and sampled everything. One of us had the 3-course meal with the roasted beef Wellington, Onion & Ale soup, and sticky toffee pudding‚Äîabsolutely perfect from start to finish. Everything was delicious, and next time we‚Äôre definitely getting extra dessert‚Ä¶ one to share was NOT enough! The fish and chips and the Wagyu burger were also amazing. Five stars all around!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhB9TRa6u5CgHulg_9FJMcRc&fid=0x0:0x8a173f9aeeee6ff0"],"When":"2025-10-8"}]

[{"Name":"Jayme Warner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJhFvXV58X2fSelLyONDGXL6327ZJUrE4_zCQMMWW1xR-m0A5y7w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my second visit and I honestly don't know which meal I loved the most. My friend stuck with the fish and chips and said they were the best fries he'd ever had. The atmosphere is so fun. I love all of the history decor. The dark wood bar and floors give a nice ambiance. I also love that there is outdoor seating and "outdoor" caf√© and high top tables outside the restaurant on the main street in New York New York. Everything about Nine Fine Irishmen is great. I'll be making regular stops here when I'm in town.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhB2K5dHpocGqq_PRlVTUioK&fid=0x0:0xf765128fb8891b21"],"When":"2026-2-2"},{"Name":"Julius Kundrat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTeEe66P457AS50GarkZzQyrteEiwuOMPSn4CTdn0EH41OeHvMvQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As our last dinner in Vegas we decided to eat in this restaurant and I must say it was phenomenal. I had the chance to try the Shepard's pie and it was truly fantastic. Besides the food, the waitress Kevin was an incredible guy. He was extremely polite, helped us with everything and took some nice pictures for us. If you want to have a great steak or some Irish traditional food, this is the place to book a table at.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBD1r2cqZRgrRjIhOTrqjIa&fid=0x0:0xf765128fb8891b21"],"When":"2026-2-6"},{"Name":"Shelby Robidoux","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGRBPLbfBFyYCVEINSo1SSh4e2K05EMAqSEp5_HI6t4GKo8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"THE HOST WAS RUDE but THE FOOD WAS GREAT!!!

We came up to the stand and she asked if we had reservations. I apologized and said ‚ÄúI didn‚Äôt know we needed them‚Äù. She replied in a snarky tone ‚Äúalways‚Äù so we started to walk away. Then she said ‚Äútable for 2?‚Äù I was confused because she just told us we needed reservations. When I asked for clarification she said ‚Äúwell, we can take walk ins too‚Äù I found her comments unnecessary and her tone off putting. I hope she doesn‚Äôt treat all the guests like that.

I had the bangers and mash, so delicious!! Great snap of the pork bangers skins, yummy gravy with mushrooms and creamy potatoes. My mom had the Irish cheesestake, she said it was pretty good but wasn‚Äôt a fan of the beer cheese. I also enjoyed an Irish margarita that was refreshing with Jameson orange. We shared the bread pudding. Oh my goodness it was so decadent. Just the right amount of sweetness, creamy texture, a little crunch on the top of caramelized sugar, and came out piping hot, so be patient and let it cool down‚Ä¶unlike us. Haha. Large portions for mains and dessert.

The atmosphere was very fun. Live music and a lady dancing an Irish jig. All the patrons were up dancing and singing too. Very lively and entertaining.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhD8RvbDKNUzmt9Rhv3gnplD&fid=0x0:0xf765128fb8891b21"],"When":"2026-1-17"},{"Name":"Gary Howell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXkf-LVjQQDK-QhDigrR_yM4HyuHcwCcbbXle35Wg3N3hZjOsADtQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best Fish and Chips I‚Äôve Had in Years

I‚Äôve had a lot of fish and chips over the years, but what I had at Nine Fine Irishmen in Las Vegas blew me away. The fish was absolutely perfect‚Äîcrispy on the outside, flaky and flavorful on the inside. It honestly might be the best fish and chips I‚Äôve had in years.

What really stood out was the attention to tradition. In true Irish fashion, they had malt vinegar on the table‚Äîbut they also served it with a fresh lemon wedge. I ended up using both, and the combination was incredible. It added just the right balance of tang and brightness to the already delicious fish.

Our waitress (I regret not getting her name) was one of the friendliest people I‚Äôve encountered on this whole trip. She made us feel completely at home, like we‚Äôd known her for years. Places like this thrive because of people like her. If anyone from management is reading this, give that woman a raise!

If you‚Äôre anywhere near the New York‚ÄìNew York Hotel & Casino on your Las Vegas trip, stop in. You won‚Äôt regret it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDQiQx4jbsjxxz8J_u30f5V&fid=0x0:0xf765128fb8891b21"],"When":"2025-11-8"},{"Name":"Brenda Fuhr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXSWkYfNhdzgSk8TzrVL_aH_Mh6qu9fFOE1zR1QCEUaaf7KAH8V=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service at the bar inside (2 in party) . Staff checked in and chatted just enough to feel like we never waited for another pint but were able to have a good break in the noise and press of the strip.

This was our second visit in our stay. Had dinner with a larger group (7) at dinner. Reservations recommended for dinner service but the hostess was able to get us in very quickly from a walk up reservation. Seated upstairs (elevator if stairs are an issue) in a large cozy booth/table which allowed for great conversation where you could easily hear everyone. Bangers and mash hit the spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDpcoQdGH5flQhG4LrKezBF&fid=0x0:0xf765128fb8891b21"],"When":"2025-11-12"},{"Name":"Stephanie Boone","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJmPY52aknFiOi47hgttOqapLjKFBcZTzlnazVUWMiJcNMm6g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely LOVE this place!!  Excellent vibes and decor.  I had the Jameson Orange Mule (craveable!) to start and had the Shepards Pie with added cheese for dinner.  Excellent!!!  Highly highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDWywJwB01OxAfI2qeKT3Yh&fid=0x0:0xf765128fb8891b21"],"When":"2025-12-16"},{"Name":"H K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqn1HQKrDi5FQ_OwlImSVZo18T_tXAerGWjdQ4Zl97dfcBAL_I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Authentic atmosphere, delicious food, and an unforgettable experience at Nine Fine Irishmen.
The moment we stepped inside, it felt like visiting an old Irish home ‚Äî the interior is so detailed and atmospheric, we kept looking around, admiring every corner. It‚Äôs clear that a lot of thought went into the design, and it really transports you.
The food was amazing ‚Äî flavorful, comforting, and served in huge portions. The beer-battered pickles were a standout, crispy and addictive. The shepherd‚Äôs pie was rich and perfectly seasoned ‚Äî we couldn‚Äôt even finish it, though it was unbelievably good.
We packed up the leftovers to take home, but they were stolen later that night in a casino. Honestly ‚Äî we understand why. That pie was worth stealing.
Highly recommend this place for anyone wanting hearty food, great vibes, and a memorable time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBQz1eLCDEnLreFO9TgkctZ&fid=0x0:0xf765128fb8891b21"],"When":"2025-7-28"},{"Name":"Jacqui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsQF80s0CU4R2ore33h95Z2ziT6u3UptePhXBxNcX40poY9YQh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"An Irish pub inside New York New York.  The lighting inside is very dim with an authentic Irish decor. There are 2 floors of seating with bar seating available as well. Seems to be a very popular spot. Our table ordered the Fish and Chips, Shepherd's pie, and I got the chicken pot pie. The chicken pot pie was made with tomato bisque, which is something I have never had before.  I liked it, but would get the Shepherd's Pie next time. The service was good/average.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBdYIFRMTi-Al3gQsUx6pDp&fid=0x0:0xf765128fb8891b21"],"When":"2025-11-23"}]

[{"Name":"Rich Gold","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXaR9pkNSBb06LfRUIccH2Csxg9wDOD-2xvvCHZXlZG9wmeO73Z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Decided to stop in to the Tilted Kilt for a light dinner and the Mac Daddy Flatbread seemed very intriguing so we gave it a try.
Since Denise is a vegetarian we asked that the meat be served on the side and they were very accommodating.
Sorry about the photo not showing the entire flatbread, we dug in to our first slices pretty quickly.
We have to say that the Mac Daddy is an excellent flatbread. We‚Äôve tried Cheeseburger Pizza at other places in the past but this beats those out hands down. The Ranch Dressing and Dill Pickles combine for an excellent flavor profile.
Be adventurous. Give it a try.
As far as the restaurant, it was a friendly atmosphere as could be expected. I was surprised that it was not at all busy, but the benefit was that our food was delivered incredibly quickly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhD6I81hUHBN8gkB_B0GqFPl&fid=0x0:0xea0c13e1411878fb"],"When":"2025-12-24"},{"Name":"Robert Degnan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVqP2fLIgSZwDV7OB_9pl7rEZjKsqQehPV2m904CtwmuUg_CqZsw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came in on a Sunday. There are over 25 tvs on with all the football games as well as golf. Huge selection of beers and full service bar. During the game they had a $3 special on Miller. We got the pulled pork, BBQ, mac n cheese. It was creamy and topped with fried onions on top. So good. We ordered 10 wings. 5 were Jamaican jerk. Unique flavor throughout. We also got 5 buffalo, garlic. The combination was really good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAh7G2qKVbowQdNfY2pFt4Z&fid=0x0:0xea0c13e1411878fb"],"When":"2025-9-28"},{"Name":"vic carr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOO6F7Zfrp-gz92v1_htBWpRMhmJJhMzxPTSrr_s7TgvGtEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Great place to sit, enjoy a variety of beers and liquor. Really good food and awesome service. Plenty of seating. If you decide to sit out the high roller ferris wheel and have a bite while catching sports highlights then this is your place. Good times.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCtQB2Qyz4keTE_3intaGkN&fid=0x0:0xea0c13e1411878fb"],"When":"2025-12-23"},{"Name":"Brian ‚ÄúBmanpitt‚Äù Pitcher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWe0MjsVWEJdzdTIqy9Ir-SaZ7A8Yq0fd7S1nANp4x-OCE_ijd70w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great atmosphere not enough servers being cute..Loved the design and interior looks like a nice Irish pub .... Way bigger and love the decor. The food was good but nothing over the top. I eat at allot of Irish bars and found them more authentic..The server was good but she was running many tables...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgMCw_ZTlrwE&fid=0x0:0xea0c13e1411878fb"],"When":"2025-3-20"},{"Name":"Frans Ponson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhN00-r56UmTCsGGi08ZUZ58K10OXP8cxcYffdUNaP8JcJfVGq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you are just like me a Chicken Wing Master then you have to eat at this restaurant. Wings where grilled just at perfection point while moist inside grispy outside, tried 3 flavors all perfect did not try anythings else but if you are a chicken wings lover just like give this restaurant a try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgMDg67n8nQE&fid=0x0:0xea0c13e1411878fb"],"When":"2025-2-27"},{"Name":"David Oliver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWujqqscekZLMq9p1tMxaHoSAiEV_YZuTiWE39rGyvuNNcefmrG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came to Las Vegas for a business trip and stopped by while hungover. I was greeted at the door immediately by Arianna with a huge smile and great attitude. The atmosphere, music, and decorations are fantastic as well. Claire was my server, and she was amazing. Great attitude and attentive, I never had to wave her down once. I was told Eli was the chef and he cooked everything perfectly. Mozzarella sticks were hot when they arrived and my burger was ACTUALLY cooked how I requested it. I wish I had staff like this in the restaurants around my town. I will definitely be back the next time I'm in town. Thank you guys so much!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgICRyMqBTg&fid=0x0:0xea0c13e1411878fb"],"When":"2023-3-23"},{"Name":"Chris Dickinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKMSs9sq9GpDKHUs0_dLue-4UH0jTDSiHE6wMyqV39oq1wj5w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered a few drinks to watch the game.  Our server tabbed us out and said her shift was over and someone else would take care of us. 45 minutes later, no one came to help.  Asked another girl and she said ‚Äúo yeah, her shift ended at 6.‚Äù  No offer to assist us, so we left.  Better places in Vegas to go, skip this place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Albranyer Hern√°ndez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIHxjFliXSw8upufmFVToMSyT3d7uNNTswLUBZRYeggvoGs_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very bad service. FYI she takes great photos!üòú","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dan N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6mZmo-hpodUdaFPcWdUKL9ZM4_Tq3XY80lOKRkzreiOUf_DBBlA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"T.A, was my boy‚Ä¶ he took care of us like family.
But I gotta say that I'm a bit disappointed with some of the lies that were told to get the sale. Peter seemed like a really nice guy. Was just trying to do his job and sell us. I'm in sales. I can respect that. However, I'm big on ethics. We were told we'd be going to Sapphire at the end, "largest strip club in vegas". I can tell you we were not taken there. Also, he sold us on the idea that they sell out every event with 100 people. Well.. There was barely MAYBE 12 people. T.A. brought the energy. Real good dude. 10/10 host. Was it fun? Yes, we made the most out of it and met some cool people. Would we do it again? There's a good chance but I gotta remove 1 star for the dishonesty to create a false time constraint to get the sale. We were already wanting to go. There is definitely a party atmosphere in this bar and is a great place to visit while in Las Vegas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgIC68ICtfw&fid=0x0:0x588874ad6dcf2d44"],"When":"2021-8-28"},{"Name":"Malcolm Naylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJutj2JhBV5tlcTFBkJVyZUQiSzMTcMhnIQOU7_1m9Jk7VSdg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Lovely little casino off the linq. [{"Name":"Keith Mills","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2iot0Ym7iHpw596_zv94V6UMtC6_EqA-KSBS0jOhu9SUOiOJF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent food. I had the veal burger one day and the Christmas Dinner another. Did not dissappoint. Also, the bread pudding is worth the wait, but if you're in a hurry, the Snickerdoodle Cookie is fantastic too. Will definitely visit this place again next time I'm in Vegas!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBwGFTj3VeOF0j7G9MkYyBg&fid=0x0:0x3a1f33dd86678c24"],"When":"2025-12-27"},{"Name":"Alexandra Kane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDEBsmmIipZQdCE-VEfJGLySgjc_f7foljwKZFJ_3L4lijq175=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Strolled by here and originally planned to pop in for a quick Guinness, and we ended up staying all afternoon. The staff was an absolute pleasure and made our afternoon. We learned a bit about Ireland! They have an large whiskey selection and we tried one I had never seen or tasted before, Guinness was on special during the Sunday NFL games, and we got half off appetizers after 3pm. We tried the potato cakes, Scotch deviled eggs, brussel sprouts with bacon, and the potato leek soup. Everything was delicious! Would definitely visit again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCNNhluXZDoa98pReCDTitM&fid=0x0:0x3a1f33dd86678c24"],"When":"2025-10-29"},{"Name":"Linh Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFRcXkPJy6AlE96pOdXN--vVrAvf2KvJ7AyOtR0_AVHwG8rw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Wonderful dinner and bar spot with amazingly friendly and attentive service. The interior and atmosphere were super nice for essentially a spot inside a food court. I‚Äôd absolutely come back just for the vibe alone

Decent food with huge portions at reasonable prices (for Vegas). Potato and leek soup was good. The fish and chips were decent‚Äîgood batter and the fish was ginormous, but the fish was a bit too dry for my liking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCwfCASnLrEo83_jtZtCUgh&fid=0x0:0x3a1f33dd86678c24"],"When":"2025-12-28"},{"Name":"Adrianna Salazar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXA5Pl9BEZHSpJOZhpipf8QCUPq8eeHgevkwRBlFN2l7sJ9hDQP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Irish pub on the strip in Mandalay Bay. Went in for happy hour - had some amazing deviled scotch eggs. I like they give you four of them and not three like some places. Add some of their spic mustard- so delicious!
They service Guinness in proper glasses and do a proper pour, letting it settle.
Lots of throwback pics around by place. Great decor and it feels like a true Irish spot.
Service was great. So friendly and helpful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAPJHpu8WMnept1eAsAhB0R&fid=0x0:0x3a1f33dd86678c24"],"When":"2025-11-29"},{"Name":"Samantha Garvie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTRHLq7IFMqk5uLdCHiBKONddnxNrviaFoXMFSmj87aKgsg50G=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for something different for dinner and was able to snag a spot at the bar. The bartender was friendly and was able to keep up with everyone as it was packed! I had the mac and cheese with blackened chicken on top for my main course and then the corned beef wontons as an appetizer. Both were very tasty and came out quickly. Prices were reasonable for Vegas and the atmosphere was fun!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhChjKbr1Ki-RMCtLsol2r63&fid=0x0:0x3a1f33dd86678c24"],"When":"2025-11-16"},{"Name":"Elizabeth Fitzgerald","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW8idw-Wek_kbiJycPM2Zh6HCfQXdkge7yKMCbWmoLKHItUv638eQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was one of our favorite spots in Vegas! We stayed at the Luxor and stopped in for dinner, and the fish and chips really hit the spot. The staff was super friendly, and what really sealed the deal was the band, Diddley Idols! They were SO fun and incredibly talented - we even came back the next night to watch them perform. We‚Äôd absolutely come back next time we‚Äôre in town.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhA8XmWqLJ87viJghUYuxeDX&fid=0x0:0x3a1f33dd86678c24"],"When":"2026-1-14"},{"Name":"John Quist","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_80m5TI0dsKsw0S8rm34G9TSmcvMmqOXRp385lm63BEqH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were surprisingly pleased with the fabulous fish and chips. They even baked my fish, rather than deep fry it, and happily allowed me to substitute a garden salad for the French fries. On another occasion, I ordered salmon and was impressed by the style of preparation and the flavor. When in Vegas, visit R√≠ R√° Irish Pub.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhC7O2lnWTE_NjYwoQqrhfxM&fid=0x0:0x3a1f33dd86678c24"],"When":"2025-10-12"},{"Name":"Steve Bintley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUz91tVXj2WT6I7ulfH4Gp5APOIk3cPC3KNiD2RZ0AT-lIBXQFCDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing pub and restaurant and will certainly be returning. It‚Äôs absolutely huge inside with loads of options available for large groups too. From the greeting staff through to the waiting staff throughout the meal, the service was exceptional. Recommendations were given which were perfect and even proactive comments on the happy hour deals were greatly appreciated. The decor throughout is traditional and the tables clean and spacious. There‚Äôs screens showing sport but they don‚Äôt take over from the atmosphere already present.

There‚Äôs a good choice on the menu for both food and drinks. The scotch egg appetiser was really delicious and a huge portion. I opted for a shrimp dish from the specials menu which was equally as tasty, with good vegetables, sauce which wasn‚Äôt over powering and decent sized shrimp.

The previous positive reviews are well justified and I‚Äôd recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCipIkohV_-lhP0W3rdOfwD&fid=0x0:0x3a1f33dd86678c24"],"When":"2025-8-19"}]

[{"Name":"Cheryl N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVw52mR7ryOF9nrqVv7fa8ZYYQYvDBrOV6humAlXtmXIWzloXQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ok, it's a little run down & a little sketchy, but that's not a fear factor for us.

It has great decor inside, including many football clubs. There is bar, bar table, and counter-like seating, as well as a dining table area. It is not a large space.

So the bartender told us about a weird restriction for their license. We were ordering cocktails, so we couldn't transact that sale at the bar. We had to sit at a table away from the bar to order and received the cocktails. It wasn't a goof. 2 couples came in, and one of the 4 had to stand away from the 3 at the bar because he had a mixed drink. Weird zoning laws??

Still, it was a good, unique experience and we would return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBAzEwcAZBXgSVuopPdiTSc&fid=0x0:0x97338c714f4ba773"],"When":"2025-11-23"},{"Name":"Kat Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKxMMHmg_OeP7tv2IafRMBOmJuo5tq5zftYEFrkpE0lO05QQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Been wanting to try it out. $21.00 for 1 piece of cod and French fries is pricey in my opinion. The waitress forgot to bring our appetizer, but remembered when she brought out our main entrees.  I guess better late than never??? The place is in an older building and needs some TLC.
Would we return? Maybe on a Monday when it's 'AYCE' fish and chips for $21.00.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDbKTjg-RyTQRlVFQ6qq1zr&fid=0x0:0x97338c714f4ba773"],"When":"2025-11-10"},{"Name":"Summer Brew","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvPDmKSG5phpvAt9sLSb2xlV_sd94EioNkN-5F6KaUgjn0_6Vb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A rare, English pub hidden in China Town. Inside there is a dark, hole-in-the-wall vibe. I got the traditional fish and chips dish and my husband ordered the Banger in a Bun, with a side of chips. The food was delicious - no notes. For drinks, I ordered a Snake Bite, which is pear cider and Guinness and husband ordered Harp on tap. Drinks were delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDmkSR-PgnlGaZ9UqVw55UT&fid=0x0:0x97338c714f4ba773"],"When":"2025-8-29"},{"Name":"Nerual Locke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPHAeyLmMPp7n26NOnuDeSbcQKm9k666hLTEq-XXwFlU3rLTFX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An authentic British pub serving authentic British food.  Great gaming, specials and food.   See you there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDyrqUVTLSh4qTGhalAtR9n&fid=0x0:0x97338c714f4ba773"],"When":"2025-9-9"},{"Name":"FrenchToast MashedPotatoes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWke01BVqWQY-y5wwdL3FMMvr9slnvMQ24tjD0T-EAjU2it8po3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Still a great place to eat every time Im in Vegas. Got the scotch egg, Cornish pastie and some fries with gravy!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBDEGK-yynmbjH_vLTWSpXc&fid=0x0:0x97338c714f4ba773"],"When":"2025-8-16"},{"Name":"Zenon Skyy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI2Zj8GaHkA5uOg-7-XR3PBRYEThlS8vAifeL2Iio0ER0qqRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Update on 4/27/25

Hi. I think that your place is great.

However, if I could make some suggestions to improving the outside of your establishment to make it look less run down.

1) Did you know that you have several bullet holes in the windows facing Spring Mountain? Yes, three.
2) Also, two of them have graffiti on them.
3) Both of the lanterns look pretty damaged.
4) Some of the glass on your side door facing east is broken.
5) The British flag lens on your sign facing west is missing.
6) The lettering on the sign on your back wall could use a fresh coat of paint.

Keep up the good food and drinks though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgICh2djr2gE&fid=0x0:0x97338c714f4ba773"],"When":"2023-2-16"},{"Name":"Herms ‚ÄúHERMS671‚Äù H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJpJWF0LoGGgETgFXEQvJH2MEDhHbT23DolJlei63kA7X1Dpm7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place actually surprised me. A friend of mine wanted to try the place out because he was wanting English pub food. We walked in and it looked like a typical pub and I didn't have high hopes for the food. The server, who was also the bartender was very informative if the menu and was able to provide recommendations. In the end, we ordered the steak and mushroom pie, chicken and leek pie, and the garlic and mushrooms app, We were blown away by the freshness and tastiness the food. Anybody looking for English pub food must try this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgIDfgsC1Ug&fid=0x0:0x97338c714f4ba773"],"When":"2025-1-4"},{"Name":"Sativa Sean Las Vegas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqEKb68nxsdGjwY3qmYdCghZ8BVFIfQ9KwwIM2V2oC0SpxENw-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the only true authentic club in all of Las Vegas! All others are pretend. It has a real English menu with English food,..it's been here since 1995...and ive been getting drunk here since then ;) I'm here now. The ONLY place to watch Soccer, especially the world cup. Spacious parking,...right across from UNLV and near a tire store and circle K...get gas right after getting lit and then park ur car and take an Uber!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgIDLnsravAE&fid=0x0:0x97338c714f4ba773"],"When":"2024-6-27"}]

[{"Name":"Antonio J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYSwVmjuQ0RDK36eyd6PquJx0hG9XS4EOhPsUNcJ6zOqyBOlZTgA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pour 24's Hidden Gem: Alain the Amazing Bartender

There's one reason Pour 24 at New York New York has become a must-visit for us: Alain, the bartender. His exceptional service keeps us coming back for more. He's not just friendly, he's attentive and makes every visit enjoyable.

Sure, Pour 24 might not be the trendiest spot on the Strip. But genuine hospitality like Alain's makes all the difference.

Plus, they offer a solid selection of draft beers, including local brews, and can whip up a mean cocktail. And let's not forget the view ‚Äì the bar offers a prime spot for people-watching on the casino floor.

For a relaxed atmosphere, good drinks, and amazing service, look no further than Pour 24. But ask for Alain ‚Äì he'll make your experience unforgettable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgIDD49B1&fid=0x0:0x6e625b804d6f0ae5"],"When":"2024-4-13"},{"Name":"Kyle Lawhon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvkYsZ5Lj_aVvqfUAwcfQyq1MlaYsGbQrj4vATj2Kz2Ufy6k0P=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great bar for descent priced drinks on the strip. Have good rap selection and a happy hour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCP0Limj1ZsLqKFuqfzXHCM&fid=0x0:0x6e625b804d6f0ae5"],"When":"2025-12-19"},{"Name":"Danielle Sr.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfP7NeXTl7UMTfsEw6Sop2tcozfncG3Og8yMz3HqLApj79lrZorg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Located inside the New York hotel. I didn‚Äôt like my first round of drink but the bartender was so kind as to remake me new drinks. Kind customer service‚Ä¶ smooth vibes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgMCw_cuyWw&fid=0x0:0x6e625b804d6f0ae5"],"When":"2025-3-20"},{"Name":"Brad Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmqN8uVmkqqKOAD8wf5hexTMUH7NYyB3Wu_vz8aTGa53VA1BPC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Mango Carte again! This great beer is tapped everywhere in Vegas. The bar is out in the atrium level, between pedestrian walkways, and so can be pretty noisy. The view into the casino is pretty good, and this is a great place to people watch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgICjw6KYmAE&fid=0x0:0x6e625b804d6f0ae5"],"When":"2024-4-25"},{"Name":"Free Humans","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUvtU_gkBap4TvKVMCu21YuI5kyCzremsvsdssKpnfRVFAZHI3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you're looking for the only good beer in las vegas, this might be the place. Let me qualify,  i'm from Wisconsin so the corporate swill at 99% of vegas places is unacceptable. At NYNY there are two choices, a delicious brown ale at 8.3% and Founders breakfast ale same abv. And you get a view of the losers on the gambling floor.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"JC C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWutKsEyeP_S84mvVxnQHL4lU20QCvt8nCJndmi5Ycw3wWNWG8I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The coldest beer in the strip!!
After a long walk in Las Vegas, Boulevard is a must to stop at least for an ice cold beer at New York, New York's Pour 24.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgIDL2b3c8wE&fid=0x0:0x6e625b804d6f0ae5"],"When":"2024-6-28"},{"Name":"Steve Bintley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUz91tVXj2WT6I7ulfH4Gp5APOIk3cPC3KNiD2RZ0AT-lIBXQFCDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Small bar with the only seating being the stools round the bar itself, but it‚Äôs a good spot for a drink and people watching. There‚Äôs a number of TV screens for catching up on the sport and the views down over the casino are unique. They have a Happy Hour Mon-Thurs between 12 and 3pm which makes the prices very good, and the range of drinks on offer is extensive. While the staff weren‚Äôt overly friendly during my visit they were fast with the service and quick to spot when you needed a refill! It‚Äôs a great touch for there to be wireless charging pads on the bar for phones too. I‚Äôll certainly be returning next time I‚Äôm in the hotel.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgID9-cDoIw&fid=0x0:0x6e625b804d6f0ae5"],"When":"2024-3-18"},{"Name":"Richard Veale","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVESGUxhaVUQwCBEgMRh7H5Kry3wGnUuMbZ-xgjGOt6IwW_V5gW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really can't beat this bar. It overlooks the casino floor, has plenty of TVs and even more beer varieties.  Pictured: Kilt Lifter.
As a Charger fan, I especially appreciated the fact that our Bartender (Mike, I think) had a Chargers jersey on. Love that !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgIDZpK6ulwE&fid=0x0:0x6e625b804d6f0ae5"],"When":"2023-9-24"}]

[{"Name":"Jasper Pan√©","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWE_c-YkQZhUA9WLQz1XxqRsyzwvi6ES5es3_RzbcPt6qqCBFcJNw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Rock house was a good bar and restaurant. It‚Äôs a sizable venue that accommodates various party sizes. Our particular private event was curtain off and we were able to enjoy a private experience despite it being connected to the rest of the restaurant. There is also a live stage that you can enjoy on certain days. Staff were accommodating and anticipated our needs. I highly recommend it. Food and drinks in this restaurant is not extraordinary. But it is above average and is what you would expect from a venue like this.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBffL7i8CNLu378J3JWJMfQ&fid=0x0:0xf749f2a5b250ffe7"],"When":"2026-1-20"},{"Name":"Dave Danekas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjKuLRH23OL3f6DZnSDVHfaUsEBmrRX3u8U41eHDMYGsOZFms=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were heading to an event at the Sphere  and popped in to grab lunch. We were seated right away and got some cocktails ordered. If you're a fan of espresso drinks, I found The Shakedown delightful. The stoli vanilla and kahlua combine to make it so balanced and smooth you definitely want more.  We went with the Mac Burger and Western 50/50. I found the combo of burger and pork patty with their BBQ sauce make the 50/50 a flavor winner!  The burger prices are low for the Vegas strip, but sides are sold separate.  We just ordered fries to share.  Our server was friendly and we liked the overall vibe of the place.  It's certainly worth checkin' out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhArI4XoEU2Bt41MERZpIP66&fid=0x0:0xf749f2a5b250ffe7"],"When":"2025-10-18"},{"Name":"Blake West","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiaR1wzqh3eQOZe4P-NH2YtvWVnmZH9pGQEu_cAC8UMxsz4TD-8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice place.  Walked in and sat at the bar while waiting for a show to start at the Sphere.  Ordered the Western 50/50 Burger and onion rings.  The beef & pork patties, with extra pork (bacon) were juicy and full of flavor.  The onion rings were large, plentiful and tasty.  Service was friendly, food was a bit slower than expected but not finger chewing late.  It was a good visit and I would go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhB8a6s9y42fn4oSsYeXGuDm&fid=0x0:0xf749f2a5b250ffe7"],"When":"2025-8-21"},{"Name":"Jenah Winkler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwr4fiFbpdeucsMIyZWwv2I0JSEPtN6DYTHXuDHMc-GgXKCTMtfg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's loud here today but it can't be helped when there is a conference group getting Together üòÑ. I asked for a Taste the Randow and the bartender has never made it before.  It come out looking like a cup of water you use to wash your paint brushes in. It may not be pretty but it is good. The hamburger sliders are good so are the chicken tacos. The vegetarian egg tastes good to. I am a happy camper. The staff is great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEPbds6Pq38mh0QE&fid=0x0:0xf749f2a5b250ffe7"],"When":"2025-5-8"},{"Name":"John P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI_CxPzu3UPAAHeERGMTVR9qQE2x60JpvFcr6APF9_ZVCLP2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amanda and Freddy, amazing staff. Such courteous professional service. Wings, pretzel bites, and buffalo cauliflower very good.Beer cheese as good as anywhere. They carry all sports packages. TV audio very loud and clear. Great decor and ambiance.  Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCxBhtqvotLYq5hfGU2vfUc&fid=0x0:0xf749f2a5b250ffe7"],"When":"2025-9-26"},{"Name":"Valerie Marquez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVcA0cgtg0f1yvh9syu2mVbRyp51yCkDJsa3PiszPzVFRtXQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stayed the night at the Palazzo so this spot is any easy walk from our suite. It‚Äôs off of Las Vegas Blvd so that‚Äôs a plus too.
Had a 50oz. to share with a friend.
Service was great!
Wings and quesadillas could‚Äôve been cooked a bit more, but flavor was alright.
Wedge salad was delish!
Good spot to meet up with friends if you don‚Äôt want to leave your hotel.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBWhRmmgiNBsdVlKC9R4xuQ&fid=0x0:0xf749f2a5b250ffe7"],"When":"2025-6-28"},{"Name":"Gen Meneo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXdpU1xSafC68Lbs2x7za7bQy7Rar7WhT8XhU3SywQn9d7gFY9h=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ended up at Rockhouse this weekend, oddly looking for a place to hang out for a bit that had beer pong.  We didn't have any expectations other than some drinks and hopefully beer pong without a super long wait.  Ended up having a great time and enjoyed good food and great drink prices.  Timing wise we hit it perfectly for happy hour and drink and appetizer specials (the beer cheese and spinach artichoke dip were delish).  Angelique was our server and she was SO nice and super attentive - super fun personality and with our larger group of 8 she hit everyone's requests perfectly.  We didn't wait long for any refills and she got us quickly set up for beer pong.  Ended up being a fun afternoon and will definitely go back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"barbara kuliak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIF1gKSBxqQOjayh1jTOBGyNfcYH_2gdwAB_f7Hcv_IP8rCpQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best bar/restaurant ever. We were there 7 times in 4 days for food, drinks, games and fun. Both Alex bartenders are marvelous. We are not big whiskey drinkers but we went for a flight and every time we went we tried a different kind. The Shibui was worth every penny. The atmosphere is welcoming friendly and engaging. Shout out to Sean Alex 1 Alex2 and Lance. Thanks for the great time","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Brown Girl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlEym2gnN6_dXgRL90zD58v_SXMPlK2qHpQMGXlmvnhVCNRjVT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Waited for bartender for nearly thirty minutes before she came out of the bathroom.And then went straight into the back area.I'm not sure where that was maybe a beer stocking area.But never once did she look up at the bar to see if She had a new customer. There was only three or four other people in there, It was evening time, but clearly I waited a long time to even be acknowledged. It was well over thirty minutes before she even acknowledged my presence.And once she did, she gave me a beer and then a little while later I asked for another drink, and in small talk, she proceeded to tell me she was the assistant manager, and I relayed the same thing to her about how I'd been there for a good thirty minutes before she had came back to the bar area., and she tesponded with \"Well , when nature calls, you gotta go, \u0026 the door shouldve been locked.\" But i did press the buzzer b4 i tealized door was not licked. And i'm pretty patient, but I had pushed the button to get in the door which was unlocked, but either way, the buzzer had went off, but never was checked on until thirty plus minutes later. That could be dangerous for other customers at the bar or the bartender or anybody who is in the establishment. If I happen to be some crazy deranged person, not to mention the key was in the drawer of the till, which was left unattended, so if I was a robber, I could have clearly went right around the bar opened.The drawer and took all the money and she would not have been none the wiser just more of a safety issue than anything.But the atmosphere in that bar is quiet and peaceful and a good place to just go and relax and have a beer or two on my way to my home, Because I live near there.  I go there about once or twice a week, but usually on day shift or graveyard early a.m. and those 2 bartenders , Samantha, and I believe the male at night is Cody but not sure either way those two are efficient. And friendly every time I go there.  Thanks for your service, and attentiveness.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael T. Ross","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlKcDA06aOWjQmEBiNgepMTj555n8_TZAu3X-VQ5vn0p2br1Dz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time at this location and will definitely be coming back here. These are the reasons why. My server Elisia (sp?) was very friendly and brought me an amazing breakfast which you can get 24 hours. Love that.
