Portion is huge. It‚Äôs afternoon snack time so we ordered the chicken fingers and fries to share. Sadly we are unable to finish the plate. There are around 6-7 pieces of chicken fingers and tons of fries. We got the homey mustard sauce and buffalo sauce. The sauce is as good as the ones from Raising Cain.
Server Nancy is the sweetest lady ever.

I‚Äôll come back tomorrow to try other stuff.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhC9n3x2AVuew31tAMJWKXcm&fid=0x0:0xdabe5b542be4a552"],"When":"2025-12-17"},{"Name":"Erica Becerra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJB9gXp6J9eUintHn1-VLctE-t5mj_F9LTTb2VZKRREKUvQ7A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here, we usually go to wolfgang puck, but since we ate there last night no one wanted to go there againü´©‚Ä¶. However this was a great choice!
On the first round we ordered the ribeye, the steak sandwich and the chicken strips.. EVERYTHING was delicious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCXaPJXvYYhby-PkHsdsFdf&fid=0x0:0xdabe5b542be4a552"],"When":"2025-11-30"},{"Name":"Sylvia Ruiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9NzH5okdPRHWep3kxvmH806a7z9TiaVpMenOKmY3D5gZLLb532g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had the street corn and cheeseburger, corn was ok but not authentic corn, but for a bar it was decent and flavor wasn‚Äôt bad. The cheeseburger was good and would order again.. fries were very good.
Beer was cold, and bartender Harro (might be misspelling) was attentive. We didn‚Äôt have much time so was a great on the run sit down meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBWZEF4R8-Sis7tToc6aFL_&fid=0x0:0xdabe5b542be4a552"],"When":"2026-1-4"},{"Name":"Kiira Penrose","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhID9QfkTZBp7FNLnssc_QxnzINKTIm24zrutS9hKm6Et2TAfz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was really good but nothing that stood out. We had the bbq wings and loaded steak fries. Our server was super friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCoZF3PekUVKMFGhFLnYgvr&fid=0x0:0xdabe5b542be4a552"],"When":"2026-1-15"},{"Name":"L & I","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWukCQhiaeX2Bj1vFHpiPeupfYWAUeM8tT-x7GUjRBJD5VLbtbvKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I really wanted to like TAP at MGM‚Äîand to be fair, the service is excellent. The staff is welcoming, attentive, and the overall vibe of the place is energetic. The menu is clean and easy to navigate, and the food pictures online look great. It‚Äôs also reasonably priced, especially for a spot right on the casino floor.

But when it comes to the food, unfortunately, it just didn‚Äôt deliver. The burger was a letdown‚Äîit lacked flavor, and the meat didn‚Äôt taste fresh. The nachos were another miss: the meat was tough, and the cheese didn‚Äôt melt well or blend with the chips. Everything tasted rushed and forgettable.

This place is big and always busy, so it honestly felt like the kitchen was just mass-producing food without much care for quality. Nothing we ordered felt special or satisfying.

If you‚Äôre looking for good service, quick bites, and a loud sports bar atmosphere, TAP checks those boxes. But if you're coming in for a memorable meal, you might want to explore other options at MGM.

Overall, I‚Äôd give it 2 stars for the food, but props to the staff for their great hospitality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgMDIoLKQsgE&fid=0x0:0xdabe5b542be4a552"],"When":"2025-4-6"},{"Name":"Sue Chef","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0D3pXZ0GZCYf4zh-5FJH5u4zRxvwf3_MUT1ayqipePgp2o2_w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you're looking for a 5-star upscale hoity-toity ritzy Las Vegas experience, this is not your place. But if you're hungry and want a quick bite to reserve your dollars and time for the slots, shows or other pursuits the town has to offer, this is it. We stopped in after our flight to town and just wanted some quick eats that didn't set us back the $$$$ that so many restaurants around here display (read that: boku bucks). We were pleasantly surprised! We had the chicken tacos (delish) and a Caesar salad (expected) with wine. The food and drinks came really fast (insert smiley face here) and the portions were large. But the delight was -- major shout out here -- KATT, our server. She was friendly, helpful and so personable! Table service (food deliverers and table clearers) were super friendly too. We ordered dessert to go, which was yummy later at the hotel but FYI the dessert portions are small. Good for us, but might be a disappointment to others and are not sharable size. All in all, this place is a 5-star *in its class.* It's a good tap bar with good tap-bar eats and treats. Atmosphere is relaxing and fun with TVs everywhere and a large open kitchen. I'm really glad it's available for the weary, hungry and thirsty casually-dressed travelers that we were. Now on to Viva Las Vegas!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nathan Martin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoLHBzYMWu8c0ou0B6rmdqbRCcKZkniwtG2nxqJQm_T4TwwZeunA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place. Good prices for Vegas! Fun light atmosphere. Good TVs for watching sports. Chris was a terrific server! Professional and attentive. Always showed up when we needed something without intruding on our meal. Highly recommended","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCUZp37q-rwBVIwgBhQ-2mc&fid=0x0:0xdabe5b542be4a552"],"When":"2025-9-26"},{"Name":"Jerifaye Flores","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2OM2fN3LBnvDj0YhT5QMr7Ojwdn8pqcIUG57l_SFTKVFgIg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were pleasantly suprised at how good the food was in this place. We were on a staycation at MGM Grand and was looking for somewhere to burn our $100 dining credit and settled on Tap bar. We were seated right away and our server approached us promptly and asked for drink orders. We ended up sharing the 3 for $33 with the spinach artichoke dip, a cheeseburger, and a Michelob ultra. It was more than enough food for the 2 of us, but we do have smaller appetites. The bill ended up being $50 with tip, so we still had half of our credit left which we didn't even get to use. The best part of this place? The Las Vegas Aces memorabilia hanging on the wall... like an entire section of it. It's very rare to see that, especially in a Strip restaurant. Yay to Tap! We will definitely be back.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Patricia Holden","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIz-w7xKl7LTiPITZmcFL4lJQPWTuL8ViXpMYC7hPhmS3ks=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We're visiting Vegas and wanted a casual dinner. We chose O'Aces and are glad we did.

My husband had a BLT with toasted Sourdough bread. The Sourdough bread was perfect.

I chose the Oriental Chicken Salad. Both were oh-so-good. Everything was fresh and the dressing wasn't just poured on the top, but the salad was tossed in it. The chicken was bite size. Delicious!

Our server Mike was attentive and friendly. We enjoyed talking with him. He made us feel very comfortable. He is definitely an asset.

There are TV's everywhere to watch whatever game is playing.

It's a cool place. If we lived here it would be our home base.

Update: We had breakfast the next morning here. Excellent! Miranda came to our table immediately and brought us coffee. She was friendly and welcoming  Our server was Bunny. She was so bubbly and happy that it was contagious. ‚ò∫Ô∏è

Our eggs, potatoes and Sourdough toast were perfect. The coffee was delicious.

The pricing was not your Vegas strip pricing. It's very reasonable.

Stop by when you're in Vegas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDY0qtriQZG5pif8A9eR7g7&fid=0x0:0xb12b433f77416e57"],"When":"2025-10-3"},{"Name":"Daniel Mula","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLs50MPDid-ulB3KrxUv54Yu4m2hpYcczcmMG44r8Hy6CjDUQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super new and classy high end bar located inside the Durango hotel and casino. üé∞
Recommend checking out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCkuBEo3Ofrc8qRE7-PYkHa&fid=0x0:0xb12b433f77416e57"],"When":"2026-2-1"},{"Name":"Cheryl N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVw52mR7ryOF9nrqVv7fa8ZYYQYvDBrOV6humAlXtmXIWzloXQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"O'Aces Bar & Grill is the typical bar/dining/gaming establishment, but the food is top-notch.

We both ordered the Cobb Salad. It came with tons of chicken, bleu cheese, bacon and tomatoes, with avocado and hard-boiled egg. The bacon bits were nice and crispy. The lettuce with some spinach were really well chilled.

So the dining area is cut off from the bar area. You can see many tvs to watch the game or probably any sport. Booths and tables are available.

Service is friendly and attentive.

If you're looking for good food along with your cocktails,  O'Aces is your place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDej9d20ZA2PinxfrmtX6Kc&fid=0x0:0xb12b433f77416e57"],"When":"2025-8-20"},{"Name":"lace m","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-tfIfaYMi8suLW7XJkAmHrbhApmkz301wwZM-ZRMtEOhe9nBl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great service, low-key mellow spot with good music playing. We really enjoyed walking around and pretending to be in Paris, France, which is on our bucket list to do. All staff were friendly and helpful.

This place is really fun to see. You feel like you are in Paris for sure. There are several restaurants like Vanderpumps, the Cafe Americano, the Eifel Tower, and Mon Ami Gabi. [{"Name":"Erika Avina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRz6NFsh5K1GbRytrs2ns2CaTgTGZWqmA1RM7FVdwEvTyvBz5uHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place was my favorite spot from all at the New York New York! I had zero desire to give them any time of tip, or even care to see them perform. The second time they switched out, we left. They just completely brought down the energy in the room. Would go back to see Adam and Marty, but if those guys are there, we‚Äôd leave after the first set. Terrible personality fit for that type of work.

Cover was $20. I didn‚Äôt see it posted anywhere. The drinks were good. 1st: Expect it to get LOUD (and ask for earplugs if u need them.)  Due to that: The TABLES desperately need a simple, numbered drink menu in large font, so u can just POINT to order drinks. (I was only served Sprite all night b/c server never asked if I‚Äôd like to change it up ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"justin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLSKo8QQQr92t4qnDL_CiVLT4GXSTzHggwAK6bMQaOAsl6BHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great time here. The staff were genuinely friendly and attentive from start to finish and made the whole experience easy and relaxed. It is a comfortable spot to sit, take your time, and actually enjoy the meal without feeling rushed.

The cheeseburger was excellent. Well cooked, juicy, and full of flavor, with everything working together nicely (apologies for the picture I only remembered when I was halfway through the burger üòÇ) Definitely one of the better casual burgers I have had on the Strip. Drinks were solid and the overall atmosphere was lively without being chaotic.

A really good option at the Luxor with great service, good food, and a welcoming vibe. Would absolutely come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCOZZ5GNg9kxt3zgLGXdF5t&fid=0x0:0x9e32057f790e7fbb"],"When":"2026-1-28"},{"Name":"Liann Amagan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXO40HRuuM_E9btxFD4_1E5SUUvCyojdDb_hNIluB_k3nhuX-wcFw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We stayed at the Luxor to watch the Chris Brown concert and it was such a convenient location being walking distance to the Allegiant Stadium. We wanted to watch the niners game on a Sunday but didn‚Äôt want to go somewhere too packed so we noticed they had a restaurant that showed the games and had multiple screens. We were able to make a reservation off of Google maps when searching this spot. We also got to request which game we wanted to watch. There were plenty of screens and areas to watch and they set up your table area for your game. We originally had a reservation for 6 but they were accommodating and our party was as larger as 8-9 at a point. They have all American food here. I got the standard burger which came with 2 Pattie‚Äôs, for $6 more you could add an appetizer and a shale. So I got the spinach and artichoke dip and my friend took my vanilla milkshake. My friends also got onion rings, nachos, mashed potatoes. They allow you to sit there for the entire game and you don‚Äôt feel pressured to leave. They do charge for extra ranch. They also have a full bar. You can also order room service and use your room credit from here too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBpxuGc95Sn0YNtEly-YY0r&fid=0x0:0x9e32057f790e7fbb"],"When":"2025-10-2"},{"Name":"Sihan Goi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDcDzu4KCSnmoZRidIGkDu13oXlwRo9t96S7mcolayFc7TcKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome dinner here with colleagues. Our best meal so far in Vegas. The ribeye was a very generous 12oz, and there was also a very generous portion of broccolini and mashed potatoes. I asked for medium rare but some parts were medium well, but it was still pretty good. The BBQ ribs were fall off the bone good as well. Also had buffalo and bourbon BBQ wings. Both were good with the ranch and blue cheese sauces. Service was good as well, and ambience is that of a sports bar.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBGsLbfNh5zOu_R83eyG04f&fid=0x0:0x9e32057f790e7fbb"],"When":"2025-8-4"},{"Name":"Lindsay Aiello","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUENswoh5eubyTLiVskrDGdoorYT6Sc7yvcOeS6ToYzNuyMJAf3OQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food, atmosphere and service was fantastic! The burger was solid, two of us got steaks (cooked rare, delicious but broccoli undercooked and under seasoned), our fish fry orderer is used to fish fry in Wisconsin so his expectations were higher than Public House could meet, and the Chicken BLT sandwich was highly favored as delicious with complex flavors and layers. Our server was Lisa and she's the best! She was so sweet and attentive. The prices were very reasonable. The drinks were good, a little weak, but well mixed.  The cheesecake has glitter!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgMDwksKdBQ&fid=0x0:0x9e32057f790e7fbb"],"When":"2025-3-25"},{"Name":"Jacob Mason","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxeCBuCqpnk6-K5K45BWZAM3aGOCKee_mPjDzwbpH8pv-8qIzaKg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Went in for a quick bite. I ordered the Standard burger with fries and the wife got the chicken tenders. The first red flag was the food was ready in 5 minutes, assumed they didn't have a ton of orders because it was fairly empty on a Thursday. Everything looked good at first.

The real issue came with the burger ($25). I get 3 bites in and I noticed my top patty was bright pink and the bottom patty fully cooked. I bring this up to our server once he finally showed up after 10 minutes to check on us. First said was "how did you order it?" And I'm like you didn't ask. So then I get the whole well the usual cook is well done (my bottom patty) and the pink one looks like medium well....

Then he offers to bring me a new burger and I said I'm good. I ate the rest of the burger and not in the mood for a whole new burger. He insists and takes my whole plate. Less than 5 minutes later I'm brought a literal single patty on a plate and a bowl of fries. Did they think I was just gonna eat a plain patty?????

DO NOT RECOMMEND THIS PLACE!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKELzmiOKa4PnxxwE&fid=0x0:0x9e32057f790e7fbb"],"When":"2025-5-16"},{"Name":"K Nicole","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLGcuhY5GBVxh2OmGEeYutYYxsZKrr8B9lOxTwoBKxGZMkKWGw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I got wings. $25 for wings but no sides.
I had Mango habanero and lemon pepper.. both were seasoned good. crispy and fresh. Best wings I‚Äôve had In a while. The service was good and food came out fast. Menu is very basic/limited. Mainly just bar food and the mixed drinks are basically $20 a piece. I liked it but pricey for simple bar food.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessica Yankulin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXY-IZ3oaUCoXCVsrjQbnk6qdXEQLClujpldpBmWJiuG8l9F8Et=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Stopped in here for dinner with friends. This is not my typical go to for type of restaurant, but it had good reviews and no real wait for a table. I also wasn't overly hungry, so wasn't feeling very particular about what we had. The service here was very good. Our server was attentive and friendly. They also have a great on tap selection, as well as bottled beers, and a decent wine list. For food, I had the Caesar salad and my friends had the Big Texan burger and the chicken fingers. Everything was decent. Nothing really stood out as great or overly interesting, but it was tasty and nicely presented. If you're looking for an easy, fairly quick meal, this is a good spot to grab a bite to eat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgIDHwdqsfQ&fid=0x0:0x9e32057f790e7fbb"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Marcy Trevino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9EeYMe7xj8NBVJtFPTha5p9zsFKvEcP3FxG-r-gdaiDdqWaY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Loved the ambience of this place, but there is a long wait. at 5 PM is when they open,we got sat down like 20min later  and then we didn‚Äôt get our food till like an hour and 20 minutes. That‚Äôs the only downside maybe because we were a big party of 12 but we‚Äôve gone to Logan‚Äòs back at home in Texas and it‚Äôll take that long..But one thing I will say the food is phenomenal. I had the fish and chips which was very delicious. The fillet was very fresh. The breading was crunchy and crispy. I love the fries so good and the ranch tasted like they made it from scratch.
The prices are not bad. The portions are big. There‚Äôs no kids menu so we have to get like regular chicken strips or like a regular adult burger, but the burger was huge very delicious though cooked the perfection. Definitely do recommend if you have time to wait.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The double zero cannoli is a deconstructed version and it‚Äôs the perfect crunchy, sweet, salty and creamy combination. It was yummy and delicious! This place and its food is incredible delightful, delicious and decadent!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAbx9L6GWxG3bv_hYbBKGb2&fid=0x0:0xc154d1d800aea095"],"When":"2025-9-2"},{"Name":"Eddie Gutierrez Jr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXfsGn5xtzKD2fJlzehnUfBIVmBjhUm0zg9JME9xUNVdSLjG39ywg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5/5 star experience. I was lucky enough to come on a not so busy night but I‚Äôd definitely recommend placing a reservation in advance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhAyi8pPJZ94MgWNjplvucd-&fid=0x0:0xc154d1d800aea095"],"When":"2025-12-3"},{"Name":"Marielle Irene dela Cruz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBlR-3F3eTXb0brNsL3o4C5D2J6hwT5uRtf3bj2y9St6307H6o=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came across a feature on this place on Facebook some time ago and since it‚Äôs not in my area, I waited to check it out. Being by myself, I couldn‚Äôt order a lot but I couldn‚Äôt decide among the red and white sauce pizzas (plus, J noted they have wagyu carpaccio that my son would love for next time)!
